description:
In recent weeks, Indonesia has been rocked by massive anti-government demonstrations. The protests are led by students, workers and womens rights groups angered by the yawning gap between Indonesias elites and shrinking middle class, and turned violent after a delivery driver was killed amid a police crackdown. John Yang speaks with The Economists Aaron Connelly about the ongoing situation.
